10 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 427.5b of Title 63, unless there
12 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
14 for the Oklahoma Medical Marijuana Authority to be designated the
15 “Oklahoma Medical Marijuana Land Reclamation Revolving Fund”. The
16 fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year
17 limitations, and shall consist of all monies received by the
18 Authority from land reclamation fees collected pursuant to the
19 Oklahoma Medical Marijuana and Patient Protection Act. All monies
20 accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby appropriated and may
21 be budgeted and expended by the Oklahoma Medical Marijuana Authority
22 for the purposes provided for in this section. Expenditures from
23 the fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
24 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
Req. No. 17349 Page 23

1 Offi ce of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
2 payment. Up to Five Million Dollars ($5,000,000.00) of the funds
3 received by and credited to the fund may be used and expended by the
4 Oklahoma Medical Marijuana Authority for environmental remediation
5 and redevelopment projects. Any remaining funds shall be deposited
6 in the General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury.
7 SECTION 3. REPEALER Section 2, Chapter 41, O.S.L. 2023
8 (63 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 427.26), is hereby repealed.
9 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
